doc.previous: Over 100 Oxford alumni were elected to the House of Commons in 2010 107 This includes current Leader of the Opposition Ed Miliband and numerous members of the cabinet and shadow cabinet Additionally over 140 Oxonians sit in the House of Lords 14
doc.after: At least 30 other international leaders have been educated at Oxford 14 This number includes Harald V of Norway 108 Abdullah II of Jordan 14 four Prime Ministers of Australia John Gorton Malcolm Fraser Bob Hawke and Tony Abbott 109 110 111 two Prime Ministers of Canada Lester B Pearson and John Turner 14 112 two Prime Ministers of India Manmohan Singh and Indira Gandhi although she did not finish her degree 14 113 five Prime Ministers of Pakistan Liaquat Ali Khan Huseyn Shaheed Suhrawardy Sir Feroz Khan Noon Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto and Benazir Bhutto 14 S W R D Bandaranaike former Prime Minister of Ceylon Norman Washington Manley of Jamaica 114 Eric Williams Prime Minister of Trinidad and Tobago lvaro Uribe Colombia s former President Abhisit Vejjajiva former Prime Minister of Thailand and Bill Clinton the first President of the United States to have attended Oxford he attended as a Rhodes Scholar 14 115 Arthur Mutambara Deputy Prime Minister of Zimbabwe was a Rhodes Scholar in 1991 Festus Mogae former president of Botswana was a student at University College The Burmese democracy activist and Nobel laureate Aung San Suu Kyi was a student of St Hugh s College 116
